<subSubSection box="[199,1072,1722,1749]" pageId="7" pageNumber="430" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1578,2037]" box="[199,1072,1722,1749]" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1722,1748]" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the name of the 
<typeStatus box="[927,975,1723,1749]" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="430" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1578,2037]" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1758,1784]" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species differs from most of its congeners by having short and broad embolus (
<emphasis box="[1406,1429,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">vs</emphasis>
. filamentous). It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2021" box="[481,608,1795,1821]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Trygetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="430" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="susianus">
<emphasis box="[481,497,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[512,608,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">susianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(the only other 
<taxonomicName box="[797,983,1794,1820]" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis box="[797,893,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">Trygetus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in the region with known male) by the different shape of RTA (cf. 
<figureCitation box="[458,702,1830,1856]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[314,1288,188,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-30@10.[265,1323,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male palps of Trygetus nakhchivanicus sp. n. (A–B) and T. susianus Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2021 (C–D). A, C retrolateral; B, D ventral. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683499/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">Fig. 9A–B and 9C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="431" pageId="7" pageNumber="430" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1578,2037]" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1866,1892]" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[593,720,1866,1893]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1846,1870]" captionTargetBox="[154,1435,348,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-87@6.[151,1436,345,1822]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Habitus of Trygetus gromovi Marusik, 2011 (A–D), T. susianus Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2021 (E), T. cyrus sp. n. (F) and T. nakhchivanicus sp. n. (G, H). A, F female, dorsal; B same, lateral; C female’s abdomen and posterior part of cephalothorax, ventral; D female’s cephalothorax, anterior; E, H male, dorsal; G same, ventral. Scale bars = 0.2 mm, unless stated otherwise." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683485" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683485/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="430">Fig. 5G–H</figureCitation>
. Total length 2.00. Carapace 0.85 long, 0.58 wide. Eye sizes: AME: 0.08, ALE: 0.04, PLE: 0.04. Carapace, sternum, labium, chelicerae and maxillae light brown. Legs yellowish, without annulations. Abdomen with dorsal and ventral scuta; dorsally grayish and with scattered dark patches, ventrally yellowish. Spinnerets pale, uniform in color. Measurements of legs: I: 2.07 (0.59, 0.21, 0.45, 0.43, 0.39), II: 1.70 (0.44, 0.20, 0.36, 0.35, 0.35), III: 1.60 (0.42, 0.20, 0.30, 0.34, 0.34), IV: 2.27 (0.59, 0.25, 0.48, 0.53, 0.42).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">
Palp as in 
<figureCitation box="[315,440,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1437,1461]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,669,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-256@8.[151,1436,669,1414]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. SEM images of the male palp of Trygetus nakhchivanicus sp. n. A anteroventral; B ventral; C retrolateral. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683491/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Figs 7A–C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[451,521,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[314,1288,188,1905]" captionTargetId="figure-30@10.[265,1323,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male palps of Trygetus nakhchivanicus sp. n. (A–B) and T. susianus Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2021 (C–D). A, C retrolateral; B, D ventral. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683499" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683499/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">9A–B</figureCitation>
; femur 3 times longer than wide, 1.33 times shorter than cymbium; patella almost as long as wide; tibia short, about twice shorter than wide; RTA slightly longer that tibia’s length, bent dorsally, sharply pointed, originating from ventromedial part of tibia; cymbium unmodified, 2 times longer than wide; bulb almost as long as wide; tegular apophysis (
<emphasis box="[629,656,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Ta</emphasis>
) about 1/3 of tegulum’s length, with 3 lobes, claw-like prolateral part, ventral and retrolateral rounded lobes; conductor (
<emphasis box="[712,745,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Co</emphasis>
), if present, indistinct; embolus (
<emphasis box="[1116,1153,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Em</emphasis>
) broad, originating at a 9 o’clock position and terminating at a 1 o’clock position.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,645]" box="[199,414,367,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="431" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,645]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,402,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Comments.</emphasis>
There is another species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Jocque" authorityYear="1991" box="[663,759,403,428]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Trygetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[663,759,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Trygetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry box="[947,1073,403,429]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
, namely 
<taxonomicName authority="Marusik &amp; Guseinov, 2003" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Guseinov" authorityYear="2003" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Trygetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacksoni">
<emphasis box="[1178,1194,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1209,1302,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Jacksoni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Marusik, Y. M. &amp; Guseinov, E." pageId="8" pageNumber="431" pagination="29 - 46" refId="ref6489" refString="Marusik, Y. M. &amp; Guseinov, E. (2003) Spiders (Arachnida: Aranei) of Azerbaijan. 1. New family and genus records. Arthropoda Selecta, 12, 29 - 46." type="journal article" year="2003">Marusik &amp; Guseinov, 2003</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is currently known only based on female (
<bibRefCitation author="Marusik, Y. M. &amp; Guseinov, E." box="[912,1227,439,465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" pagination="29 - 46" refId="ref6489" refString="Marusik, Y. M. &amp; Guseinov, E. (2003) Spiders (Arachnida: Aranei) of Azerbaijan. 1. New family and genus records. Arthropoda Selecta, 12, 29 - 46." type="journal article" year="2003">Marusik &amp; Guseinov 2003</bibRefCitation>
). Considering that there is more than 
<quantity box="[367,454,475,501]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" unit="km" value="370.0">370 km</quantity>
of aerial distance between the 
<typeStatus box="[811,859,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authority="Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2022" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2022" box="[993,1199,475,501]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Trygetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nakhchivanicus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[993,1009,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1025,1199,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">nakhchivanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1208,1273,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1208,1273,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marusik &amp; Guseinov" authorityYear="2003" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Trygetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jacksoni">
<emphasis box="[1414,1430,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,244,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">Jacksoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(almost the same as between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2021" box="[582,708,511,537]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Trygetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="susianus">
<emphasis box="[582,598,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[612,708,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">susianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Zamani &amp; Marusik, 2022" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2022" box="[764,855,511,537]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Trygetus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyrus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[764,780,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[794,855,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">cyrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[862,926,511,537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[862,926,511,537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="431" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), we decided to describe the present material as a new species; still, there is a possibility that the two populations belong to the same species. This matter should be revisited once both sexes are collected together.
</paragraph>
